content: Here's my spending data: 3 weeks ago, I spent $70 at H&M on a pair of distressed denim jeans and a white linen shirt. A few days later, I spent $120 at Sephora on skincare products. The next weekend, I spent $80 on Adidas sneakers and $20 on kitchen gadgets at the outlet mall. Last week, I spent $220 on clothing at ASOS. This past weekend, I spent $50 on candles and soaps at the farmer's market. Oh, and last month, I spent $15 on a vintage denim jacket at a garage sale.
